## Pydantic v2 conventions

- Use `model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)` on response schemas
- Separate request and response schemas — never reuse the same class for both
- Never expose `password_hash`, `git_token`, `yjs_state`, `llm_api_key`, or `embedding_api_key` in any response schema
- Use `UUID` not `str` for ID fields
- Use `datetime` not `str` for timestamp fields
- Validate sensitive string fields: `min_length=1` on required text

## Naming convention

- `{Entity}Create` — POST request body
- `{Entity}Update` — PUT/PATCH request body
- `{Entity}Response` — API response
- `{Entity}ListResponse` — paginated list response
